  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nIf I understand correctly:\r\n\r\n[This call to `asyncio.wait`](https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/fa07b6819c7f597bb5aa7ae13614d881a84081ae/p2p/cancel_token.py#L84) will used the *default* event loop if no loop parameter is provided\r\n\r\nhttps://docs.python.org/3.5/library/asyncio-task.html#asyncio.wait\r\n\r\nIf that is the case, then in our tests, won't the cancel token be running in a different loop than other things that are using our local `event_loop` fixture?\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nChange the `wait_with_token` API needs to accept an extra optional `loop` parameter.",
